TankMine.Description: A simple mine that is placed under terrain and fitted with a pressure-sensitive plate to detonate under the weight of heavy vehicles. Mines are visible to friendlies and enemies on foot and deactivate after 48 in-game days.

ATGrenadeW.Description: An explosive flask used for melting enemy armour. This carefully designed liquid bomb explodes into a dazzling flash of molten debris upon impact.

ATRPGAmmo.Description: An armour piercing projectile used with specialized RPG launchers.

ATRPGC.Description: The Venom RPG launcher fires anti-tank charges. Its simple design makes it easy to deploy, even in high-stakes operations.

ATRPGHeavyC.Description: This shoulder-mounted heavy launcher is the first of its kind. It features heavy blast shielding and is capable of launching anti-tank charges over relatively large distances.

ATRPGIndirectAmmo.Description: An armour piercing projectile used with indirect RPG launchers.

ATRPGLightC.Description: This single-use rocket can be fired a short distance. Designed to punch holes into tanks, the Ignifist is the perfect tool for infantry anticipating armoured resistance.

ATRPGTW.Description: This variant of the Bonesaw MK.3 is specially designed for use with tripod mounts. This affords it with increased stability and maximum potential range.

ATRPGW.Description: The pride of the Warden anti-armour arsenal, the Bonesaw MK.3 has one job: to cut through the heavy metal plating of Colonial tanks.

ATRifleW.Description: The Neville is unmatched in its versatility as a portable, magazine-based anti-armour firearm.

ATRifleTC.Description: This mounted anti-tank rifle boasts improved accuracy over its free-standing counterparts. The Typhon was specifically designed with shock absorption in mind, allowing for faster, more consistent firing patterns.

Aluminum.Description: Aluminum can be refined into Aluminum Alloy, which is used in the prototyping process for items.

AluminumA.Description: Aluminum Alloy can be used to produce Item Prototypes at the Engineering Center.

AssaultRifleAmmo.Description: Standard ammunition for Storm Rifles and Armoured Cars.

AssaultRifleHeavyC.Description: This unique assault rifle includes a high-capacity drum magazine designed for sustained rapid fire.

AssaultRifleHeavyW.Description: The Booker is a high-impact three-round burst Storm Rifle for those who like to shoot first.

AssaultRifleW.Description: Widely considered to be the first storm rifle, the Aalto is a marvel in Caoivish engineering. With its two fire modes, it can be used as a rapid-fire assault weapon or a mid-range rifle.

Cloth.Description: Resource used for building basic structures and producing items.

Bayonet.Description: Attached to the barrel of a rifle, this short blade can spear enemies in close quarters encounters.

BloodPlasma.Description: A blood component used to treat wounded soldiers on the battlefield.

RifleLightW.Description: The Blakerow is a carbine with a high rate of fire compared to its bolt-action predecessor. This increased fire rate does come at the cost of innate stopping power; however, its versatility and lightweight frame more than make up for any perceived shortcomings.

Components.Description: Components that can be salvaged into Refined Materials at a Refinery

Concrete.Description: A concrete compound that is used to build heavily fortified structures.

Copper.Description: Copper can be refined into Copper Alloy, which is used in the prototyping process for vehicles.

CopperA.Description: Copper Alloy can be used to produce Vehicle Prototypes at the Engineering Center.

CriticalSoldier.Description: A soldier that has been critically wounded on the battlefield. Deliver this soldier to a Hospital to recover Soldier Supplies.

Diesel.Description: Common fuel used to power all vehicles and resource mines.

ExplosiveLightC.Description: This unique demolition tool is a long, metal tube packed with explosives. The Hydra’s Whisper is designed to destroy out-of-reach movement impairing structures and detonate any mines along the length of the tube.

Explosive.Description: Resource used for producing heavy explosive weapons.

ExplosiveTripod.Description: A high-powered explosive charge that requires an accompanying detonator. The Havoc Charge is highly effective at demolishing large structures. The charge must be detonated via gunshot. The Havoc Charge’s true potential is unleashed when executing strategic demolitions at safe distances.

FacilityComponents1.Description: Damaged Components that can be salvaged into Components.

FlameAmmo.Description: A drum containing fuel for use with flame weapons.

FlameBackpackC.Description: Ammo for “Molten Wind” v.II Flame Torch

FlameTorchC.Description: Using a deadly mix of flammable gasses and chemical compounds, the “Molten Wind” is the Colonial Legion’s most devastating infantry weapon. Employing ancient techniques, Mesean chemists developed a technique to stabilize and weaponize liquid flames, which quickly transform any flammable structure into a raging inferno.

FlameTorchW.Description: Named for the unfortunate trees harmed in the development of this highly destructive weapon, the Willow’s Bane utilizes flammable chemicals and fires them into a concentrated stream through an open flame. This liquid flame ignites Colonial emplacements and garrisons to route infantry while reducing their defenses to a pile of ash.

GasMaskFilter.Description: When attached to a Gas Mask, this filter provides fresh air to the wearer.

GrenadeAdapter.Description: A rifle attachment that fires grenades with pneumatic force. Along with specialized grenades, it can launch standard grenades.

GrenadeC.Description: The Bomastone is a ‘stick’ style fragmentation grenade with a handle designed to aid in lobbing over moderate distances.

GrenadeLauncherC.Description: A weapon designed to launch specialty grenades over long-distances.  This modern Kraunian firearm uses advanced propulsion designed for increased efficiency due to the overall weight of the weapon and projectiles.

GrenadeLauncherTC.Description: Capable of firing different grenades, quickly and at long range, the Fissura gd.I is mobile enough for easy transport, while increasing the effectiveness of infantry ordinance.

GroundMaterials.Description: Resource used for building Roads and Foundations.

HEGrenade.Description: This densely packed, high-explosive grenade is designed to damage structures and vehicles.

HERocketAmmo.Description: Standard calibre rocket with a heavy explosive payload. Chance to ignite objects near impact.

HeavyExplosive.Description: Resource used for producing heavy explosive weapons.

ISGTC.Description: This heavy infantry cannon requires a tripod for stability. The Daucus is designed to give infantry a foothold against enemy vehicles and light fortifications or established fortified garrisons.

Iron.Description: Iron can be refined into Iron Alloy, which is used in the prototyping process for vehicles.

IronA.Description: Iron Alloy can be used to produce Vehicle Prototypes at the Engineering Center.

Crate.Description: A crate of items. These must be submitted to a stockpile before contained items can be retrieved.

AssaultRifleC.Description: A titanic light machine gun capable of scattering infantry lines with ease, the Catara is a modern weapon for the modern Colonial.

ListeningKit.Description: A device used to intercept enemy radio broadcasts transmitted from nearby sources.

LRArtilleryAmmo.Description: Standard payload used with Storm Cannons.

Lore.Description: A torn piece of paper containing a fragment of text.

MGC.Description: The Gast is a deadly but cumbersome Kraunian heavy machine gun. It is best suited to holding and defending established fortifications or garrisoned structures against encroaching infantry.

MGTC.Description: Built on the bones of the first automatic weapons introduced to the Legion, the “Lamentum” mm.IV is still quite an intimidating force to encounter on the battlefield. Boasting a large magazine and impressive active range, this mounted machinegun excels at laying down consistent suppressive fire.

MGTW.Description: Early iterations of this machinegun were built to be emplaced in bunkers and on the decks of lightly armed warships, the Ratcatcher is Harvey Malone’s first freely mountable infantry weapon designed for field use. Just like its predecessors, this heavy weapon suppresses enemy soldiers with unmatched efficiency.

MGW.Description: This heavy machine gun is bulky enough to require a steady surface to maintain stability. The Malone series of machine guns are unmatched defenders on the battlefield.

MaintenanceSupplies.Description: Supplies for maintaining structures. Store at Bases or Maintenance Tunnels to prevent decay on surrounding structures.

MiniTankAmmo.Description: Standard explosive shell used with certain small vehicles and infantry weapons.

MortarAmmoFL.Description: A long-burning flare that ignites midair to illuminate a large area and reveals enemy targets.

MortarAmmo.Description: An explosive payload used with mortar tubes.

MortarAmmoSH.Description: An payload filled with shrapnel used with mortar tubes. Devastates nearby infantry.

MortarTankAmmo.Description: A shell that is launched over short distances by a spigot mortar.

Petrol.Description: A medium grade fuel that's refined from Oil. Used as a higher end fuel for vehicles and in various applications at Facilities.

PrototypeKit.Description: Prototype parts to produce new types of equipment.

RPGTW.Description: This unique dual-barrelled RPG launcher can fire two RPG shells in relatively quick succession. This increase in firepower makes it nearly impossible for a single soldier to operate without the support of a sturdy mount.

Wood.Description: Resource used for building advanced structures and producing special items.

RelicMaterials.Description: Vehicle parts used to assemble Relic vehicles.

Revolver.Description: The Cometa T2-9 boasts remarkable stopping power for a sidearm. This Estrellan mainstay has lived through several generations due to its fine craftsmanship and design.

RifleW.Description: Standard-issue Warden rifle. This bolt-action firearm is as robust as they come and has seen over a century of use on the battlefield.

RpgAmmo.Description: A fast-moving explosive projectile used with RPG launchers.

RpgW.Description: The Cutler Launcher is capable of firing an unguided, rocket-propelled grenade over short distances with startling efficiency. Its simple design allows for easy deployment and storage.

SMGHeavyC.Description: A heavier, modern variation of the Pitch Gun, the Lionclaw performs well as a decent, all-around submachine gun designed as a primary firearm in urban and close-quarters combat operations.

SMGHeavyW.Description: This unique, heavy-duty submachine gun is not very useful on the run, but with careful aim and adequate cover, becomes a razorblade in the night.

SatchelChargeT.Description: Required to detonate Havoc Charges. The Havoc Charge must be placed before the detonator can be deployed.

Metal.Description: Salvage that can be recycled into other resources at a Refinery

SledgeHammer.Description: A tool used to salvage components from remains of old vehicles and equipment.

Sulfur.Description: Sulfur that can be refined into Heavy Explosive Materials at a Refinery

TraumaKit.Description: Used by medics to revive wounded soldiers.

Tripod.Description: A mount point for deployable infantry weapons and equipment.

WaterBucket.Description: A bucket that holds water. You can toss water onto fires to extinguish them.

WoundedCarriedPlayer.Description: A wounded player{0}. Drop this soldier off at a safe location for medical aid.

Wreckage.Description: Destroyed equipment reclaimed from the battlefield. Can be sorted into useful resources at a Refinery (using the right click context menu)

Binoculars.Description: An optical instrument used for viewing distant objects.

BunkerSupplies.Description: Supplies for maintaining structures. Store at Bases to prevent decay on surrounding Bunker/Trench structures when Garrison Supplies are not available.

GreenAsh.Description: Green Ash is an asphyxiating toxin. Inhaling it without protection will result in a quick death. Be sure to wear a gas mask with fresh filters when handling Green Ash.

Coal.Description: Chunks of raw Coal that can be refined into materials needed for production and power generation at Facilities.

FacilityCoal1.Description: Refined Coal required for various Facility processes.

FacilityMaterials1.Description: Metal beams needed to produce basic structures and vehicles at Facilities.

FacilityMaterials2.Description: Refined metal bars needed to produce advanced structures and vehicles at Facilities.

FacilityMaterials3.Description: Shaped, steel beams required for the most advanced processes at Facilities.

FacilityMaterials4.Description: Specialized metal sheets forged using Coal that are required to assemble advanced vehicles and equipment.

FacilityMaterials5.Description: Specialized metallic bars fortified with Petrol that are required to assemble advanced vehicles and equipment.

FacilityMaterials6.Description: Sulfur-enriched metallic bars that are required to assemble advanced vehicles and equipment.

FacilityMaterials7.Description: High-end steel bars, fortified with Heavy Oil that are required to assemble advanced vehicles and equipment.

FacilityMaterials8.Description: Meticulously engineered alloy beams that are required to assemble advanced vehicles and equipment.

FacilityOil1.Description: A high grade fuel that's refined from Oil. Used in a variety of applications at Facilities.

FacilityOil2.Description: Oil that has been purified and enriched for advanced Facilities processes.

Oil.Description: A raw viscous liquid that must be refined into fuel at Facilities.

PipeMaterials.Description: Used to construct various types of pipelines for transporting liquids.

FieldMGAmmo.Description: Standard ammunition for Field Machine Guns and Gunboats.

FireRocketAmmo.Description: Standard calibre rocket with an incendiary explosion. Will ignite objects near impact.

FirstAidKit.Description: Used by medics to heal other soldiers.

GrenadeW.Description: This anti-personnel fragmentation grenade is designed with pull-pin mechanics and a timed fuse for user safety. Serrations in the casing allow for a better grip and increased fragmentation effectiveness.

HELaunchedGrenade.Description: An explosive Estrellan grenade specially designed for use with handheld grenade launchers. This modern grenade boasts a larger payload and is deadly to lingering infantry and structural supports.

HMG.Description: A heavy machine gun that is capable of long range, indirect sustained fire. This weapon must be mounted on a tripod before it can be fired.

BarbedWireMaterials.Description: Used to construct Barbed Wire defenses.

MetalBeamMaterials.Description: Used to construct Metal Beam defenses.

Lore5.Description: A shredded journal entry that appears intact

Lore12.Description: A tin flask, bits of it are rusted.

In02KItem.Description: This weighted runestone has rough edges.

In03KItem.Description: A runestone with edges that cut like a blade.

In04KItem.Description: A runestone that weighs no more than a feather.

In05KItem.Description: A runestone that appears to shimmer in the dark.

Lore9.Description: A simple Loughcaster rifle, caked in blood.

Lore6.Description: Ripped segment of rough parchment. Appears to be a letter.

Lore13.Description: An old rusty shovel, caked in dried dirt.

Lore1.Description: A tin case filled with tobacco.

Lore3.Description: A barely legible, mouldy page torn from a journal.

Lore2.Description: A folded piece of paper, much of the ink is faded.

Lore7.Description: Old remains of a scout’s reconnaissance log.

Lore8.Description: Excerpt from a Warden Scout's Journal

Mortar.Description: This short-range cannon is designed to bombard enemy infantry with indirect fire.

PistolLightW.Description: This unique sidearm fires in three-round bursts. The Cascadier may not have the stopping power of its cousins, but it more than makes up for it with its lightweight frame, concealability and fire rate.

PistolC.Description: A pistol imported from Estrella in the east, the Ferro 879 is a common sight on many battlefields.

PistolW.Description: Standard issue Warden pistol. Designed by a Nevish gunsmith, the Ahti Model 2 is a reliable sidearm that any soldier should feel proud to carry.

RadioBackpack.Description: Automatically gathers map intel periodically when equipped. The Radio Backpack is also used to transmit other sensitive information across long distances.

RifleAutomaticW.Description: The precursor to the storm rifle, the Sampo Auto-Rifle, is a mastercraft of its day. With a single shot and automatic fire mode, this versatile rifle may not reach the fire rates of automatic weapons but more than makes up for it with utility.

RifleC.Description: The primary infantry rifle of the Colonial Legion. Its predecessor, The Volta Repeater, was a sturdy, reliable firearm but had many limitations, namely, fire rate. The Argenti solves this limitation as well as being more compact and lightweight.

RifleHeavyC.Description: An old war Mesean rifle. It boasts high stopping power, but not as accurate as its modern variant. A weapon of legend, the Howling Lions wielded the Volta during their raid on the beaches of Fisherman’s Row.

RifleHeavyW.Description: The weapon of choice for pirates and smugglers, its legend is well-earned. With incredibly high stopping power and unique revolver mechanism, the Hangman often plays judge, jury, and executioner.

RifleLightC.Description: This unique rifle fires three rounds in rapid succession. The Fuscina is the first of its kind, designed for laying down suppressive fire during assaults on fortified enemy entrenchments.

RifleLongC.Description: An older but reliable model of Kraunian long rifle. The Omen is a sturdy, simple weapon best used in long-distance skirmishes.

RifleLongW.Description: The Clancy Cinder is a classic, high-powered long rifle designed for use in mid-to-long range encounters. First deployed with the Hands during a high-risk operation in Acrithia.

RocketBooster.Description: A booster engine that provides thrust for launching Ballistic Rockets to long distant targets.

SMGC.Description: This classic submachine gun is sturdy and irreplacable as a general tool for close-range engagements. The Pitch Gun earned its namesake from Mesean sailors who employed the weapon to successfully defend against a night raid on the Geraston docks.

SatchelChargeW.Description: This heavy-duty explosive device is designed to deal significant damage to fortified structures and stationary vehicles.

Shotgun.Description: This close-range firearm is an Estrellan import originally designed for hunting wild game. The Brasa is primarily used in urban operations.

Shovel.Description: A tool for digging Trenches and other entrenched structures.

NoTargetText.SourceString: Not a valid location to excavate
NoTargetText.LocalizedString: Not a valid location to excavate

SmokeGrenade.Description: A standard smoke grenade designed for concealing allied movement or screening the enemy’s vision.

SniperRifleC.Description: A Kraunian rifle modified for long-range engagements. It doesn’t have the range or stopping power of other marksman rifles but more than makes up for it with unmatched reliability in a range of environments and a superior effective rate of fire.

SniperRifleW.Description: A heavy-duty, long-range marksman rifle. The Clancy-Raca has one hell of a kick but is fitted with a powerful scope, allowing infantry to survey the battlefield and provide support from a safe location.

SoldierSupplies.Description: A standard issue set of supplies for foot soldiers. Bases must be stockpiled with Soldier Supplies in order for players to spawn.

StickyBomb.Description: A adherable grenade designed to penetrate heavy tank armor. The Sticky Bomb can only be thrown a short distance and is ineffective against structures.

SMGW.Description: The Fiddler Submachine Gun is a widely used urban combat weapon. Its high rate of fire and compact frame make it ideal for close-quarters engagements.

UnexplodedOrdnance.Description: An old war artillery shell that failed to detonate. Etchings on the side indicate a powerful payload and should be handled carefully.

AmmoUniformW.Description: Warden specialists require a uniform designed to optimize their capacity to haul a variety of heavy ammunition.

ArmourUniformC.Description: A heavily reinforced vest designed to protect grenadiers from back blasts. As such, the Flak Vest reduces cuts and scrapes on top of dampening bullet impacts.

ArmourUniformW.Description: Repurposed from ancient wars, these armour plates are highly effective at stopping enemy small arms fire. That protection comes at the cost of weight, and the wearer will feel quite restricted and encumbered.

EngineerUniformC.Description: Engineers are the bones of the Mesean Republic. They are outfitted with a heavy bag and belts for easy access to tools and handheld materials.

EngineerUniformW.Description: Caoivish engineers are legendary in song and stature. They wear specialized uniforms, outfitted with belts and bags for easy access to tools and handheld materials.

GrenadeUniformC.Description: Of the most distinguished divisions of the Legion are the Grenadiers. They are outfitted with specialized satchels and pockets for maximizing their capacity to haul explosives.

MedicUniformC.Description: For medics of the Legion, this uniform has a plethora of pockets and bags designed to carry and deploy first aid gear easily.

MedicUniformW.Description: Physicians in the Warden army are unmatched and this uniform has a plethora of pockets and bags designed to carry and deploy first aid gear easily.

OfficerUniformC.Description: This uniform, while impractical in combat, denotes the head of a regiment. Appropriately dressed officers may freely discipline their subordinates. Ancient Mesean officialis were key to the Legion’s organization. This modern attire honours their lasting legacy.

OfficerUniformW.Description: A formal uniform that denotes a regiment’s leading officer. While impractical, the officer on duty may use their authority to discipline subordinates without reparation. Officers hold an important role in the Warden military, dating back to ancient times when Caoiva was ruled by a dozen kings.

RainUniformC.Description: Quite accustomed to the temperate climates of the south, Colonials wear this oilcloth jacket paired with thick boots to operate at high efficiency in all but the heaviest storms.

ScoutUniformC.Description: Legion scouts are deployed on the most dangerous missions. Their gear is lightweight, sturdy and well-suited for extended operations in rugged terrain.

ScoutUniformW.Description: The Warden army relies on outriders to provide and recieve vital intelligence. Their gear is sturdy and well-suited for extended operations in rugged terrain and inclement weather.

SnowUniformC.Description: Unaccustomed to the cold, Legionaries must always adapt. This heavy topcoat is designed to mitigate the effects of cold while still allowing for optimal mobility and combat effectiveness.

SnowUniformW.Description: Born and bred in the northern cold, this heavy parka protects Warden infantry from all but the worst blizzards.

SoldierUniformC.Description: Standard issue infantry uniform for the Colonial Legion, designed for general frontline warfare with ballistics weapons such as rifles and machine guns.

SoldierUniformW.Description: Most common Warden infantry uniform, designed for general frontline warfare with ballistics weapons such as rifles and machine guns.

TankUniformC.Description: Nothing compares to the efficiency and destructive capabilities of the Colonial armour division. Tank crew are provided with sturdy coveralls and satchel belts for easy access to essential tools required for tank maintenance and operation.

TankUniformW.Description: Caoivish armour is unmatched in its design and resilience. All crew are provided with a sturdy boilersuit and satchel belts to access essential tools required for tank maintenance and operation.

Warhead.Description: The payload for Ballistic Rockets. A high yield bomb that delivers over 3 tons of TNT and is capable of leveling an entire village or town block.

WorkHammer.Description: A tool used to build structures and assemble materials.

WorkWrench.Description: A multipurpose tool. Can be used to dismantle mines/barbed wire and unlock vehicles.

CoalField.Description: A resource field for collecting Coal to be used as fuel, for production at Facilities or taken to a Refinery.

OilField.Description: An Oil Field that can produce Oil for further refinement or for power production.

SulfurField.Description: A resource field for collecting Sulfur to be taken to a Refinery.

ComponentsField.Description: A resource field for collecting Components to be taken to a Refinery.

SalvageField.Description: A resource field for collecting Salvage to be taken to a Refinery.

ATPillbox.Description: This heavily reinforced pillbox allows the garrisoned infantry with anti-tank rifles to fire on approaching enemy armour from a safe position.

BarbedWireSpline.Description: Used to slow down enemy infantry movement. Can be dismantled with a Wrench.

CoastalGun.Description: An old coastal defence gun that has been reused for the defence of key locations against naval bombardment.

ConcreteMixer.Description: A portable device that mixes various materials to form Concrete, which are used to build heavily fortified structures.

Construction.Description: A vehicle used to build large structures.
Construction.BPConstruction_C[1].Description: A specialized vehicle designed by the Basset Motor Society used in the construction of large structures.

ConstructionYard.Description: An area where certain structures can be built and prepared for shipping.

Crane.Description: A heavy mobile Crane used to lift vehicles and very heavy equipment.
Crane.BPCrane_C[1].Description: The Basset Motor Society’s Class 2 Mobile Auto-Crane is used to lift and reposition vehicles and very heavy equipment.

DeployedGrenadeLauncherTC.Description: Capable of firing different grenades, quickly and at long range, the Fissura gd.I is mobile enough for easy transport, while increasing the effectiveness of infantry ordinance.

DeployedListeningKit.Description: A device used to intercept enemy radio broadcasts transmitted from nearby sources.

EmplacedATW.Description: A defensive emplacement with a 68mm Anti-tank cannon. This rudimentary weapon was once built to fit onto the hull of large naval vessels, but was eventually phased out and repurposed.

EmplacedHeavyArtilleryC.Description: This heavy artillery cannon is designed to cripple enemy fortifications from an entrenched position. Its long heavy barrel gives the "Thunderbolt" outstanding range.

EmplacedHeavyArtilleryW.Description: A heavy cannon designed to shatter the garrisons and fortifications of advancing forces. The Exalt is best utilized when emplaced into a defensive position to take advantage of its impressive range.

EmplacedLightArtilleryW.Description: A light artillery cannon designed to be a fixture in defensive fortifications. The Lariat sports a formidable long-range 120mm cannon designed to put immense pressure on enemy infantry.

EmplacedInfantryW.Description: The Snare Trap is a repurposed anti-aircraft flak cannon used to fortify emplaced positions with twin anti-infantry machine guns.

EngineeringCenter.Description: A research facility where players can contribute towards the research of their faction's Tech Tree.

Factory.Description: A manufacturing plant for producing military equipment.

FieldBridge.Description: A makeshift bridge for transporting light equipment over a short distance. Will take damage when vehicles drive across.

FieldHospital.Description: A field medical facility used to treat critically wounded soldiers at the front line.

FirePit.Description: A pit of fire used to keep soldiers warm during Snow Storms. Requires Diesel to fuel.

GarrisonFishHut2.Description: An abandoned building in the world that has been fortified and garrisoned.

Hospital.Description: A large medical facility for treating critically wounded soldiers returning from the battlefield.

IntelCenter.Description: A high-tech listening post designed to intercept and decode enemy transmissions. The Intelligence Center can target distant locations and will continue to decipher sensitive transmissions over a sustained period.

Keep.Description: An old Keep. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

LargeCrane.Description: The star of the BMS arsenal of military-grade construction equipment, the Overseer Sky-Hauler makes several tonnes look like a feather, and enjoys a high level of mobility while deployed along heavy-duty rail lines.
LargeCrane.BPLargeCrane_C[1].Description: The star of the BMS arsenal of military-grade construction equipment, the Overseer Sky-Hauler makes several tonnes look like a feather, and enjoys a high level of mobility while deployed along heavy-duty rail lines.

LRArtillery.Description: A heavy fixed position artillery piece that can release devastating firepower on distant enemy targets.

MGPillbox.Description: A well-fortified bunker position fitted with a mounted machinegun. Garrisoned infantry will lay down heavy suppressive fire upon approaching enemies from a fixed angle.

MagicBox.Description: A magical box that duplicates the item in its first inventory slot.

MaintenanceTunnel.Description: Prevents the decay of nearby structures when supplied.

MassProduction.Description: A manufacturing plant for large-scale production of military equipment.

Motorboat.Description: A motorized boat for moving small groups of infantry across rivers and between islands.
Motorboat.BPMotorboat_C[1].Description: Powered by the Basset Motor Society’s lightweight Grouper engine, this simple wooden boat is ideal for ferrying small groups of infantry across rivers and between islands.

ObservationTower.Description: An Observation Tower that provides intel on friendly and enemy forces in an area.

Refinery.Description: A Refinery for converting raw resources into materials.

ResourceBox.Description: A mysterious box with a never ending supply of resources

ResourceContainer.Description: A container that can carry large quantities of resources and can be transported by certain vehicles.

RiflePillbox.Description: A reinforced dugout that gives the garrisoned rifle infantry a fortified defensive position to fire on approaching enemies from relative safety.

RocketSite.Description: An abandoned launch site from the Great Wars for firing long range ballistic rockets.

Seaport.Description: A large building used to store crates, vehicles, boats, and shippable structures.

ShippingContainer.Description: A container for shipping very large quantities of Crates using Crane loaded vehicles. This type of container can only be unloaded at Storage Depots and Seaports.

SignPost.Description: A sign used to relay information to other soldiers.

StorageBox.Description: A shared storage container that can be used to stash item.

StorageFacility.Description: A large building used to store crates, vehicles, and shippable structures.

TankStop.Description: An anti-tank obstacle that prevents vehicle access to an area. Can be dismantled with a Wrench.

WatchTower.Description: Reports nearby enemy movements to players with Radios equipped

WeaponRack.Description: A rack used to mount multiple firearms.

BorderBase.Description: A small base used as a jump-off point for invading enemy regions. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

FortBaseT1.Description: A large forward operating base. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

FortBaseT2.Description: A large forward operating base. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

FortBaseT3.Description: A large forward operating base. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

ForwardBase1.Description: A temporary forward operating base. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

RelicBase1.Description: An old fort. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

TownBase1.Description: A garrisoned focal building vital for the defence of a town. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

TownBase2.Description: A garrisoned focal building vital for the defence of a town. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

TownBase3.Description: A garrisoned focal building vital for the defence of a town. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

TroopShipBase.Description: A temporary forward operating base used to stage beach landings. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

Foxhole.Description: A simple hole dug into the ground to provide infantry with makeshift cover from enemy fire.

EmplacedATLargeW.Description: Built to compliment other free-standing artillery pieces, the emplaced Huber Starbreaker launches 94.5mm shells over very long distances. A necessary tool for infantry to knock back armoured Colonial advances.

EmplacedCannonLargeC.Description: Not to be outdone by its counterparts, the 2a-1 “Ruptura” is fitted with a 75mm cannon. Designed to aid in holding ground for longer durations, the “Ruptura” is a strong, efficient anti-armour tool.

EmplacedIndirectC.Description: To combat Caoivish ingenuity, the Meseans developed their own indirect RPG propulsion system. Dual launchers are fitted on a large emplacement platform to maximize coverage in an established position, rather than being relegated to a guerrilla warfare tool.

EmplacedInfantryC.Description: Built like a saw blade, the DAE 1b-2 emplacement gun is fitted with three cascading machine gun turrets. What the "Serra" lacks in power, it makes up for in sheer rate of fire for a weapon of its size.

EmplacedMultiC.Description: The DAE 3b-2 fires rockets over long distances from a safe, emplaced position. This unique weapon was given its name due to the screams heard across the battlefield during its first deployment, with some referring to the barrage as a “web of death.”

FacilityCatwalkBridge.Description: A raised walkway for creating paths above complex Facilities.

FacilityCatwalkPlatform.Description: A raised walkway for creating paths above complex Facilities.

FacilityCatwalkStairs.Description: Stairs that connect to raised Catwalks, which create paths above complex Facilities.

FacilityCrane.Description: The Foreman is an all-purpose, no-frills, easy to assemble crane. Perfect for hauling heavy loads in facilities where loading and offloading is commonplace.

FacilityFactoryAmmo.Description: A factory for producing advanced ammo types such as large calibre shells, rockets, and flame ammo.

Description.SourceString: Produces various types of tripod weapons.
Description.LocalizedString: Produces various types of tripod weapons.

Description.SourceString: Produces various types of Rockets.
Description.LocalizedString: Produces various types of Rockets.

Description.SourceString: Produces large calibre ordnance for use with tanks and artillery.
Description.LocalizedString: Produces large calibre ordnance for use with tanks and artillery.

FacilityMineOil.Description: Extracts fuel from Crude Oil Fields. Must be constructed nearby.

Description.SourceString: A generator that leverages electricity to pump oil through attached pipes.
Description.LocalizedString: A generator that leverages electricity to pump oil through attached pipes.

Description.SourceString: A machine that opens up cracks in the earth by injecting water at a high pressure to increase the output of Crude Oil.
Description.LocalizedString: A machine that opens up cracks in the earth by injecting water at a high pressure to increase the output of Crude Oil.

FacilityMineResource1.Description: A stationary harvester that automatically gathers Salvage. Requires Petrol.

FacilityMineResource2.Description: A stationary harvester that automatically gathers Components. Requires Petrol.

Description.SourceString: An excavator that allows for the mining of Damaged Components when a Component Field is depleted
Description.LocalizedString: An excavator that allows for the mining of Damaged Components when a Component Field is depleted

FacilityMineResource3.Description: A stationary harvester that automatically gathers Sulfur using Heavy Oil as fuel.

FacilityMineResource4.Description: A stationary harvester that automatically gathers Coal. Requires Petrol.

FacilityMineWater.Description: Pumps water through pipes. Must be built on bodies of water.

Description.SourceString: A generator that pumps water more efficiently. Requires Power.
Description.LocalizedString: A generator that pumps water more efficiently. Requires Power.

FacilityModificationCenter.Description: A garage that facilitates vehicle modifications and upgrades.

FacilityPipe.Description: Industrial piping that allows for automatic transport of various liquids and fuels into a network of pipes that connect to various facility structures.

FacilityPipeOverhead.Description: Industrial piping that allows for automatic transport of various liquids and fuels. These specialized pipes can be built overhead to connect to pipe networks across areas with high traffic.

FacilityPipeUnderground.Description: Industrial piping that allows for automatic transport of various liquids and fuels. These specialized pipes can be built underground to connect to pipe networks across areas with high traffic.

FacilityPipeValve.Description: A weighted valve that controls the rate of flow through a pipeline. Requires a Wrench.

FacilityPowerDiesel.Description: A structure that generates power by burning Diesel.

Description.SourceString: A generator that burns petrol to generate more power.
Description.LocalizedString: A generator that burns petrol to generate more power.

Description.SourceString: A generator that burns coal to generate power.
Description.LocalizedString: A generator that burns coal to generate power.

FacilityPowerOil.Description: A power plant that generates a large amount of electricity using Oil or Coal.

Description.SourceString: A reactor that combines Water with Heavy Oil or refined Coke, resulting in a more pure natural gas, which in turn is more efficient at generating power. Chunks of raw Sulfur are created as a byproduct.
Description.LocalizedString: A reactor that combines Water with Heavy Oil or refined Coke, resulting in a more pure natural gas, which in turn is more efficient at generating power. Chunks of raw Sulfur are created as a byproduct.

FacilityRefinery1.Description: A factory that refines raw resources into Construction Materials for advanced facilities. Additional modifications allow for the development of a variety of different materials.

Description.SourceString: A unique factory for forging specialized machinery parts needed to construct vehicles. Requires Coke or Petrol.
Description.LocalizedString: A unique factory for forging specialized machinery parts needed to construct vehicles. Requires Coke or Petrol.

Description.SourceString: A heavy automatic press that refines materials into a denser form.
Description.LocalizedString: A heavy automatic press that refines materials into a denser form.

Description.SourceString: An assembly bay with specialized equipment for quickly building and packing materials needed on the frontline.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly bay with specialized equipment for quickly building and packing materials needed on the frontline.

Description.SourceString: An industrial smelter for melting down Salvage to remove impurities. Requires Coke.
Description.LocalizedString: An industrial smelter for melting down Salvage to remove impurities. Requires Coke.

FacilityRefinery2.Description: A factory for refining raw resources into Processed Construction Materials. Additional modifications can allow for additional refined materials needed for advanced facility operations.

Description.SourceString: Advanced sorting machinery for sifting piles of scrap metal for useful materials.
Description.LocalizedString: Advanced sorting machinery for sifting piles of scrap metal for useful materials.

Description.SourceString: A large industrial cauldron for liquefying metals to remove impurities from advanced materials.
Description.LocalizedString: A large industrial cauldron for liquefying metals to remove impurities from advanced materials.

Description.SourceString: An expanded workshop for manual process of delicate materials.
Description.LocalizedString: An expanded workshop for manual process of delicate materials.

FacilityRefineryCoal.Description: A processing plant that refines Coal into useful materials used in facility production and power.

Description.SourceString: A high powered furnace that brings Coal to high temperatures to separate out non-volatile Coke.
Description.LocalizedString: A high powered furnace that brings Coal to high temperatures to separate out non-volatile Coke.

Description.SourceString: Processing vats that refines Coal into Oil.
Description.LocalizedString: Processing vats that refines Coal into Oil.

Description.SourceString: Advanced processing vats that refine large amounts of coal into Heavy Oil.
Description.LocalizedString: Advanced processing vats that refine large amounts of coal into Heavy Oil.

FacilityRefineryOil.Description: A refinery that processes Oil into other useful materials for the purposes of production and power generation.

Description.SourceString: A large processing drum that allows for the controlled introduction of hydrogen to yield a similar output of Petrol for less raw Oil.
Description.LocalizedString: A large processing drum that allows for the controlled introduction of hydrogen to yield a similar output of Petrol for less raw Oil.

Description.SourceString: A high-heat furnace that catalyses raw oil into refined Heavy Oil.
Description.LocalizedString: A high-heat furnace that catalyses raw oil into refined Heavy Oil.

Description.SourceString: A blast furnace that further refines Heavy Oil into an Enriched Oil needed for advanced processes.
Description.LocalizedString: A blast furnace that further refines Heavy Oil into an Enriched Oil needed for advanced processes.

FacilityResourceTransfer1.Description: An open container marked for storing raw resources that can be transferred into and out of Facilities. Stockpiles may be public or reserved.

FacilityResourceTransfer2.Description: A space marked for storing refined materials that can be transferred into and out of Facilities. Stockpiles may be public or reserved.

FacilityResourceTransfer3.Description: Metal drums for storing various fuels that can be transferred into and out of Facilities. Stockpiles may be public or reserved.

FacilityRoad.Description: A temporary road used to enable vehicle access between main roads and remote bases.

FacilitySiloOil.Description: An industrial silo for storing various types of Fuel.

FacilityVehicleFactory1.Description: A standard Assembly Station for production of essential vehicles and equipment. Construction will take time and may be halted if resources are depleted. Some projects require a base vehicle to be present on the Assembly Station before production can begin.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing light-duty logistics vehicles like trucks.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing light-duty logistics vehicles like trucks.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing half-tracks and rocket vehicles.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing half-tracks and rocket vehicles.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing field weapons and utility vehicles such as Harvesters.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing field weapons and utility vehicles such as Harvesters.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing tank class vehicles.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing tank class vehicles.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing emplaced weapon platforms and specialized tanks.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing emplaced weapon platforms and specialized tanks.

FacilityVehicleFactory2.Description: A large Assembly Station for production of advanced vehicles and equipment, such as tanks and trains. Construction will take time and may be halted if resources are depleted.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing train cars.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing train cars.

Description.SourceString: An assembly station for producing heavy tank class vehicles.
Description.LocalizedString: An assembly station for producing heavy tank class vehicles.

Foundation011x2T1.Description: A foundation that provides a suitable surface for constructing Facilities.

Foundation012x2T1.Description: A foundation that provides a suitable surface for constructing Facilities.

Foundation01T1.Description: A foundation that provides a suitable surface for constructing Facilities.

Foundation02T1.Description: A foundation that provides a suitable surface for constructing Facilities.

FuelContainer.Description: A container for storing high volumes of liquids. Nearby structures and vehicles can refill directly from this container.

PowerBox.Description: A power interface for manually disabling power in a circuit.

PowerLine.Description: Conducts power between two Power Poles.

PowerPole.Description: Used to connect Power Lines. Up to 4 Power Lines can be attached to a single pole.

Description.SourceString: A light that illuminates the surrounding area. Requires at least a minimum amount of power to function.
Description.LocalizedString: A light that illuminates the surrounding area. Requires at least a minimum amount of power to function.

ATGunAIT3.Description: An entrenched AT gun manned by stationed troops.

ArtilleryAIT3.Description: An entrenched Howitzer manned by stationed troops.

FortCornerT2.Description: An underground shelter that serves as a foundation for permanent fortifications. Connects to other Bunkers and Trenches.

FortCornerT3.Description: An underground shelter that serves as a foundation for permanent fortifications. Connects to other Bunkers and Trenches.

EngineRoomT3.Description: A engineering facility that provides power to Bunker structures using pipe connections.

MGAIT2.Description: An entrenched machine gun manned by stationed troops.

MGAIT3.Description: An entrenched machine gun manned by stationed troops.

ObservationBunkerT2.Description: A radio bunker that provides intel to friendly units about the surrounding area. Reinforced with wood, it can withstand more punishment than a standard radio tower, and therefore is capable of increased effectiveness.

ObservationBunkerT3.Description: A radio bunker that provides intel to friendly units about the surrounding area. Built from solid concrete, this reliable structure can push its effective range beyond lesser fortified radio structures.

FortRampT1.Description: A ramp that enables access to underground Bunkers.

FortRampT2.Description: A ramp that enables access to underground Bunkers.

FortRampT3.Description: A ramp that enables access to underground Bunkers.

NoVisRailTrackSpline.Description: A segment of railway for train cars. Tracks can attach to or fork from existing railways to form complex networks.

PreplacedRailTrackSplineBiarc.Description: A segment of railway for train cars. Tracks can attach to or fork from existing railways to form complex networks.

PreplacedRailTrackSplineFoundation.Description: A segment of railway for train cars. Tracks can attach to or fork from existing railways to form complex networks. This type of railway can only be built on Foundations.

RailTrackSplineFoundation.Description: A segment of railway for train cars. Tracks can attach to or fork from existing railways to form complex networks. This type of railway can only be built on Foundations.

SmallRailTrackSpline.Description: A segment of railway for small gauge train cars. Tracks can attach to or fork from existing railways to form complex networks.

BarbedWireWallSpline.Description: Used to prevent enemy infantry movement through an area. This structure is difficult to destroy with conventional weapons and must be dismantled with a Wrench.

SandbagFullSpline.Description: A defensive wall that hinders enemy movement and provides cover during combat.

SandbagHalfSpline.Description: A defensive wall that hinders enemy movement and provides cover during combat.

GarrisonStation1.Description: A garrisoned strongpoint used in the defence of a town. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

GarrisonStation.Description: A garrisoned strongpoint used in the defence of a town. Players can spawn and stockpile items here.

TrenchConnectorT1.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches and Bunkers. This is a special Trench variant that can resize dynamically and can be built underneath roads.

TrenchConnectorT2.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches and Bunkers. This is a special Trench variant that can resize dynamically and can be built underneath roads.

TrenchConnectorT3.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches and Bunkers. This is a special Trench variant that can resize dynamically and can be built underneath roads.

TrenchEmpT1.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches. This variant can also serve as an emplacement for mannable defenses.

TrenchEmpT2.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches. This variant can also serve as an emplacement for mannable defenses.

TrenchEmpT3.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches. This variant can also serve as an emplacement for mannable defenses.

TrenchT2.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches and Bunkers.

TrenchT3.Description: A dugout that's used for cover and as passageways between Bunkers. Connects to other Trenches and Bunkers.

GateT1.Description: A gate that provides access to a walled off area.

GateT2.Description: A gate that provides access to a walled off area.

GateT3.Description: A gate that provides access to a walled off area.

TankStopSplineT3.Description: An anti-tank obstacle that prevents vehicle access to an area, and is resistant to most types of damage.

WallSplineT1.Description: A basic barrier that is used to prevent passage through an area.

WallSplineT2.Description: A barrier that is used to prevent passage through an area.

WallSplineT3.Description: A barrier that is used to prevent passage through an area.

ArmoredCarATW.Description: A slight variation of the V.110, the Gravekeeper comes fitted with an embedded Bonesaw launcher, transforming the humble armoured car into an effective indirect anti-armour vehicle.

ArmoredCarC.Description: Colonial Armoured Cars are quick, well-rounded urban assault platforms. These anti-infantry vehicles are equipped with twin-barrelled machineguns.

ArmoredCarFlameW.Description: While the Noble Firebrand Mk. XVII is a deadly flamethrower tank, a more efficient means of employing flame weapons was needed. Enter the Wild Jack. Named for the fiery idols made by children for Dead Harvest, the Wild Jack is a variation of the Highlander.

ArmoredCarMobilityW.Description: Fitted with all-terrain treads, the Highlander brings significant all-terrain mobility and performs especially well in snowy and mountainous environments.

ArmoredCarOffensiveC.Description: This “Xiphos” variant is fitted with a high-powered anti-tank turret in place of the twin machine gun platform.

ArmoredCarOffensiveW.Description: This early O’Brien variant, the V.101 Freeman is fitted with a 360 degree ballistics cannon turret at the expense of top speed.

ArmoredCarTwinC.Description: Fitted with twin RPG launchers, the T8 employs hit-and-run assaults against enemy structures and emplacements.

ArmoredCarTwinW.Description: One of Conor O’Brien’s best traits was his ability to modernize and make use of older technology in his designs. The v.190 Knave is the perfect example of this philosophy. Fitted with a modified, outdated twin-grenade launcher turret, the Knave is a surprising combination of speed and subterfuge that quickly routs the enemy, leaving them befuddled.

ArmoredCarW.Description: Warden Armoured Cars are quick, well-rounded urban assault platforms. These anti-infantry vehicles are equipped with twin-barrelled machineguns.

Mech.Description: Designed for the soul purpose of fighting back the cursed undead, the “Centurion” Mechanized Utility Vehicle is equipped with two high powered, heavy machine guns and a deadly, front-facing cannon.

MediumTank2MultiW.Description: Colm Gallagher’s engineers designed a variation of the Outlaw that features an independently rotating MG turret sitting atop the main armament of twin anti-tank cannons. What it lacks in raw firepower compared to its older sibling, the Highwayman more than makes up for it with versatility.

RelicAPC.Description: An armoured landship reinforced with an alloy now lost to time. This nearly indestructible beast carries up to 8 passengers. Whispers of its existence date back to the first breaching.

RelicArmouredCar.Description: A recovered Colonial prototype once found in early mechanized warfare. Built on the frame of a powerful tractor, this amoured vehicle was seen escorting soldiers or, later, in support of larger armoured forces.

RelicLightTank.Description: A light armoured mechanized vehicle first seen in early border skirmishes between Caoiva and Veli. With its thin frame, it was deployed in wide formations, often overwhelming enemy forces.

RelicMediumTank.Description: Ancient by modern standards, this first iteration heavily armoured Colonial Assault tank is fitted with full coverage shielding and equipped with twin sponson cannons.

RelicScoutVehicle.Description: A vehicle once used by officers to survey the battlefield, or to deliver emergency supplies and orders.

RelicTruck.Description: A sturdy old farmer's truck that's been reinforced for military use.

BattleTankATC.Description: A heavy Lance variation, the 25, or “Hasta”, was employed in the first siege on Brightwall, a city now colloquially referred to as, “The Blemish”. Bombarded by heavy, armoured resistance in northern Veli, Colonial tank regiments requested a heavy vehicle with more effective search and destroy capabilities. Fitted with a front-facing 94.5mm cannon, the “Hasta” is a more than capable tank destroyer.

BattleTankC.Description: A heavy-duty Battle Tank with thick armour plating and destructive firepower. The Lance is fitted with a 75mm turret and a front-facing 12.7mm anti-infantry machine gun. The heavy armour limits top speed, but in exchange it can take a lot of punishment.

BattleTankW.Description: A heavy-duty Battle Tank with thick armour plating and destructive firepower. The Flood is fitted with a 75mm turret and a front-facing 12.7mm anti-infantry machine gun. The heavy armour limits top speed, but in exchange it can take a lot of punishment.

BattleTankDefensiveW.Description: The Juggernaut is a heavily armoured Flood variant fitted with a heavy flamethrower turret that fires an advanced adhesive propellant. Its shovel-like treads may hinder top speeds, but this beast is quite capable in extreme weather conditions.

DestroyerTankFlameW.Description: In response to the Legion embarking on aggressive northern offensives, the Firebrand is designed to conflagrate and eradicate their garrisons with ease. Built using the aggressive frame of the Widow, the Firebrand is a pure force of nature when paired with a secondary armoured escort.

DestroyerTankW.Description: This deadly tank turns predator into prey. A tank Destroyer, the Noble Widow specializes in ambush tactics, waiting for its quarry and striking with destructive high-velocity shells.

FieldATC.Description: The "Battering Ram" is a mobile Anti-Tank field gun firing 68mm armour-piercing rounds.

FieldATW.Description: The Collins Cannon is a mobile Anti-Tank field gun firing 68mm armour-piercing rounds.

FieldATLargeC.Description: The “Stygian Bolt” Heavy Field Gun is fitted with a monstrous 94.5mm cannon paired with heavy angled blast shielding. Inspired by the rows of narrow canyons in their homeland of the Lacrista province, Mesean engineers designed this field weapon to keep its crew as safe from ancillary fire as possible while maintaining forward momentum.

FieldLightArtilleryC.Description: A long range Colonial mobile artillery used to lay siege to fortified positions.

FieldCannonDamageC.Description: Armed with explosive 40mm rounds, the Smelter is perfect for engaging enemy armour. The frontal blast shielding provides operators with ample cover during heated skirmishes.

FieldCannonLargeW.Description: This robust field cannon not only allows infantry to fire heavy 75mm shells with ease, but it provides state-of-the-art curved blast shielding for maximum protection from crossfire.

FieldCannonW.Description: This destructive short-ranged cannon is designed for direct engagement with enemy fortifications. The Wolfhound is fitted with reinforced shielding and a 40mm barrel.

FieldMGC.Description: A dual barrelled, high calibre anti-infantry machine gun. The “Sagittarii” is fitted with forward-facing armour plating and is excellent for suppression.

FieldMGW.Description: A dual barrelled, high calibre anti-infantry machine gun. The Swallowtail is fitted with forward-facing armour plating and is excellent for suppression.

FieldMortarW.Description: A heavy mobile mortar platform fitted with a thick frontal shield for assaulting fortified locations.

FieldMultiW.Description: Lyle Rycker first built a prototype of the Wasp Nest as a test for his rack mounted rocket batteries that would eventually find their way onto armoured vehicles. Capable of firing twelve compact rockets in quick succession, the Wasp Nest became a quick favourite of the Warden infantry testing it, so an official design was requisitioned.

FieldATDamageW.Description: The Rampart is a powerful field cannon capable of dealing devastating damage to all but the heaviest of armoured vehicles while providing its crew with comprehensive ballistic shielding.

GunboatC.Description: A naval vessel designed to bombard coastal targets. The "Charon" is fitted with a 120mm light artillery cannon and a 12.7mm Machinegun.

GunboatOffensiveW.Description: The Meteora Gunship replaces the machinegun with another identical 120mm artillery cannon on the bow.

GunboatW.Description: A naval vessel designed to bombard coastal targets. The Ronan is fitted with a 120mm light artillery cannon and a 12.7mm Machinegun.

HalfTrackArtilleryC.Description: This “Javelin” variant is fitted with a 360 degree mortar platform, designed to support infantry in frontline operations.

HalfTrackC.Description: Designed for escort missions and to support infantry operations, the HH-a class “Javelin” Half-Track is an armoured, versatile all-terrain vehicle that can be equipped with a variety of mounted weapons.

HalfTrackDefensiveC.Description: With reinforced armour at the expense of speed, the "Hoplite" is a formidable force in the heat of combat.

HalfTrackOffensiveW.Description: Fitted with a heavy-duty anti-tank gun, the Blinder is capable of punching through all but the most tempered of alloys.

HalfTrackW.DisplayName: Niska Mk. I Gun Motor Carriage
HalfTrackW.Description: Designed for escort missions and to support infantry operations, the Niska Gun Motor Carriage Half-Track is an armoured, versatile all-terrain vehicle that can be equipped with a variety of mounted weapons.

HalftrackMultiW.Description: A first of its kind, the Skycaller is a variation of the Niska Motor Carriage with a Rycker designed rocket battery fitted in the rear bed. This unique armoured vehicle quickly fires rockets over long distances with ease, and can be rearmed and relocated at the drop of a hat. The Skycaller is the deadly result of combined Nevish and Caoivish engineering.

LandingCraftC.Description: The "Acheron" is an armoured amphibious vehicle designed for carrying troops across large bodies of water to aid in coordinated beach landings and flanking assaults.

LandingCraftOffensiveC.Description: With its mounted machinegun, the "Doru" is the perfect addition to any shoreline assault.

LandingCraftW.Description: The Mulloy Landing Personnel Carrier is an armoured amphibious vehicle designed for carrying troops across large bodies of water to aid in coordinated beach landings and flanking assaults.

LightTankArtilleryW.Description: A modified Devitt fitted with a specialized Caine mortar turret at the expense of top speed.

LightTankC.Description: A highly maneuverable lightweight tank. Designed for urban environments, the “Hatchet” is fitted with a 40mm cannon.

LightTankDefensiveW.Description: The Ironhide Light Tank is similar to the Mk. III but reinforced with plates of heavy steel at the expense of speed and maneuverability.

LightTankFlameC.Description: This modified “Hatchet” features a reinforced fuel cell fixed to its rear alongside a flamethrower turret. This light tank can launch litres of burning fuel a fair distance, while its crew remains protected behind light armour plating.

LightTankMobilityC.Description: The “Kranesca” Light Tank is fitted with an overpowered engine and a reinforced chassis, capable of boosting its top speed at the expense of overall acceleration and maneuverability.

LightTankW.Description: A highly maneuverable lightweight tank. Designed for urban environments, the Devitt is fitted with a 40mm cannon.

LightTankOffensiveC.Description: The “Pelekys” H-class light tank is heavily modified with an open top chassis and equipped with a devastating long-range anti-tank cannon.

AmbulanceC.Description: The “Salus” Ambulance is efficient at transporting Critically Wounded Soldiers and carrying medical supplies.

AmbulanceFlameC.Description: This simple variant of the “Salus” ambulance is fitted with a high-powered hose designed to quell wildfires.

AmbulanceFlameW.Description: A simple variant of the Dunne Responder 3e that’s fitted with a high-powered hose designed to extinguish raging flames.

AmbulanceW.Description: The Responder Ambulance is efficient at transporting Critically Wounded Soldiers and carrying medical supplies.

Barge.Description: A large shipping vessel, the Aquatipper is used to transport vehicles, equipment, and personnel over large bodies of water.

Bicycle.Description: A simple, old-style Blumfield bicycle. This is a smaller recreation model, designed for short-distance sprints.

BusC.Description: The “Chariot” is a transport vehicle used to shuttle personnel to the front line.

BusW.Description: The Caravaner is a transport vehicle used to shuttle personnel to the front line.

ConstructionUtility.Description: An advanced variant of the Universal Assembly Rig, the BMS - Fabricator is fitted with a unique kit designed to handle advanced or specialized construction and excavation jobs.

FlatbedTruck.Description: A heavy duty shipping transport truck designed by Bassett Motor Society. It’s built for hauling the heaviest of equipment over long distances with ease.

Freighter.Description: The Basset Motor Society’s Ironship-class shipping vessel is used to freight shippable goods and heavy vehicles.

Harvester.Description: The Scrap Hauler, designed by the Bassett Motor Society is a heavy-duty piece of machinery designed to reduce scrap metal and other materials into usable, raw resources. Scrap Haulers are often used to extract battlefield resources following skirmishes.

OilTankerC.Description: The “Stolon” Tanker is a heavier R-series rig designed to transport and distribute large quantities of Fuel.

OilTankerW.Description: The Fuelrunner is a heavy Dunne rig designed to transport and distribute large quantities of Fuel.

TroopShip.Description: A heavily armoured vessel, the Basset Motor Society’s White Whale-class troop transports can deploy on faraway beaches to function as a permanent forward operating base.

MechW.Description: Built in response to the ongoing use of the Cursed in military skirmishes, the Scourge Hunter class Quadruped Mechanized Walker is equipped with a quad-barrelled rocket launcher, accompanied by a specially designed quad-barrel machine gun.

MediumTank2C.Description: Unlike the 85-series, the "Bardiche" sports a heavier, more durable build and is fitted with a coaxial heavy machinegun along with a powerful, short-barrelled 68mm turret. Modern Kraunian engineering allows for a fast reload, making it an ideal tool to combat enemy armour.

MediumTank2IndirectW.Description: Armed with a rack of Bonesaw mortar launchers, the Thornfall is designed to launch an indirect mechanized assault on enemy armour. This unique vehicle supports an allied assault and cannot withstand large amounts of punishment.

MediumTank2RangeW.Description: Originally designed in response to increasing swarms of Mesean armour, the Outlaw is an exceptionally capable medium tank armed with a long-range 40mm turret and includes a built-in storm rifle support position.

MediumTank2TwinC.Description: This evolution of the “Bardiche” is fitted quad-mounted RPG launchers paired with a high-velocity 12.7mm cannon. The “Ranseur” indicates progress in Kraunian design as they continue to leverage outdated equipment to create deadly, modern armour.

MediumTankATW.Description: A cut down variation of the Silverhand Assault Tank that sacrifices armour and protection in favour of a high-powered 94.5mm cannon. This open-top weapon platform is uniquely designed to intercept enemy armour before they’re given time to retaliate. Its moniker is a tribute to the maiming of the great king the Silverhand is named for; while his title was stripped, and his pride damaged, his rage was never quelled.

MediumTankC.Description: Designed for mass-production in Kraunia, this assault tank features a modular turret system for maximum versatility. The “Falchion” class features a powerful if understated, 40mm cannon.

MediumTankLargeC.Description: The "Talos" is a Velian modification to the 85-series, fitted with an oversized 75mm cannon. Knowing that such a heavy cannon would likely not be suitable, the engineers built it to disperse weight in such a manner that the 85-series chassis could bear it.

MediumTankOffensiveC.Description: The “Spatha” assault tank features a unique and destructive 40mm turret that fires high-velocity shells. This specialized turret is not as well suited to mass-production as its more refined counterpart, the “Falchion.”

MediumTankW.Description: The Silverhand assault tank is fitted with destructive dual-barrel armaments, and heavy frontal and rear armour. Its 68mm frontal cannon is paired with a lighter 40mm turret.

MediumTankSiegeW.Description: The Chieftan assault tank is fitted with asymmetrical armaments, including a 250mm mortar cannon and a twin-barrelled 12.7mm turret.

LightTank2InfantryC.Description: The “Scorpion” HC-class tank is a moderately armoured infantry support vehicle with twin, high-powered heavy machine guns and short-range radios for improved intelligence support. In addition, exterior seating is available for infantry.

MortarTankC.Description: The HC-Class “Ballista” is a heavy tank designed to obliterate opposition defenses with its 250mm Hades Mortar Cannon.

MotorcycleC.Description: A motorcycle and sidecar used to patrol large areas. Speed can be boosted at the cost of additional fuel.

MotorcycleOffensiveC.Description: The cab of this Motorcycle is fitted with an LMG for fast-response hit and run assaults.

MotorcycleW.Description: A Warden motorcycle used in patrols and fitted with a sidecar. The Kivela Power Wheel can also gain a momentary speed boost by burning additional fuel.

TrainLRArtillery.Description: All the power of a stationary Storm Cannon, but easily relocated via rails. This devastating cannon is capable of leveling enemy fortifications at very large distances.

SmallTrainDump.Description: A small gauge container car for transporting raw materials.

SmallTrainEngine.Description: The Mineseeker is the Bassett Motor Society’s mechanized mule. This small 0-4-0 locomotive can haul tonnes of weight over short distances with little overhead. Ideal for a mining operation or short-range supply chains.

SmallTrainFuelContainer.Description: The Tinderbox is a simple car used for transporting liquids between facilities.

SmallTrainResourcePlatform.Description: A low profile flatbed car for transporting large resources and munitions over short distances on small gauge tracks.

TrainCaboose.Description: A simple caboose that allows rail crews to maintain tracks more efficiently.

TrainCoal.Description: A container car for transporting coal to refuel trains over long-distance trips.

TrainCombatCarC.Description: Known across the colonies as King of the Rails, this heavily armoured train car is designed to protect and exert dominance over contested rail lines, especially when transporting supplies into contested territory as well as safely transporting infantry. This armoured beast boasts a forward facing cannon, as well as heavy lateral guns.

TrainCombatCarW.Description: In his later years, O’Brien nearly died in an attack on a military passenger train while travelling to Whedon’s Row. In response, he put his team to work designing not only an infantry car that offered powerful protection to any locomotive, but one that just the sight of it would run off all but the most committed of attackers—Namely its thick armour plating and powerful twin turrets.

TrainEngine.Description: One of the most storied mass-market 0-6-2 locomotives engineered by the Bassett Motor Society, this coal-powered industrial train engine is reliable, tested, and incredibly durable. The Black Bolt’s legacy is unmatched having aided the Bassett Motor Society in supplying countries across the globe.

TrainFlatbed.Description: A flatbed car for transporting large resources and munitions by train over long-distances.

TrainInfantry.Description: An armoured train car with a mounted machinegun position for transporting infantry safely over long distances.

ScoutTankOffensiveW.Description: A heavily armoured variant of the King Spire, the Gallant Mk. II boasts a weighty 30mm cannon at the cost of top speed.

ScoutTankW.Description: This small tank has been recently recommissioned to the Warden arsenal. It boasts high maneuverability and an antenna that allows for long-range communications during high-stakes recon operations.

ScoutVehicleMobilityC.Description: This stripped down Light Utility Vehicle provides extra seating for a small crew to engage in hit and run tactics.

ScoutVehicleOffensiveC.Description: This RPG-mounted Light Utility Vehicle provides a heavy-duty weapons platform with superior speed. Perfectly suited for assaulting enemy structures and vehicles, or supporting an armoured assault.

ScoutVehicleOffensiveW.Description: This LMG-mounted Light Utility Vehicle provides a heavy-duty weapons platform with superior speed. Perfectly suited for supporting flanking infantry or an armoured assault.

ScoutVehicleUtilityC.Description: This simple, modified Utility Vehicle is fitted with a reinforced hatch to provide one crew member with increased visibility for intense recon operations.

ScoutVehicleUtilityW.Description: This amphibious Light Utility Vehicle has been heavily modified to cross rivers and lakes with ease. Venturing out into the open sea is ill-advised, however.

ScoutVehicleW.Description: A multipurpose off-road Warden vehicle that can scout nearby targets.

SuperTankC.Description: Armed with a dual 75mm turret, what the “Ares” lacks in speed and versatility, it more than makes up for with raw destructive power. Development of the “Ares” was fraught with strife, and its history is intertwined with a period of several riots erupting on the streets of Dimiourg. Rebels commandeered the first “Ares” Prototype, the O-75a, and turned it against Colonial forces in the region, ultimately leading to its destruction—albeit not without great effort. This event wove the great behemoth into the tapestry of Colonial legend.

SuperTankW.Description: This gargantuan beast is the brainchild of Gray Cullen. Once thought impossible, the Predator was Cullen’s idea of how a great ship might operate on land. It boasts two sets of quad-barrelled grenade launches and a heavy-duty 94.5mm forward facing cannon. While limitations of ground-based travel posed certain restrictions on the scope of the project, Cullen wasn’t deterred and made necessary adjustments to meet his vision of the ideal land ship.

TanketteC.Description: This complete overhaul of the T3 Armoured Car is reinforced with tank armour. While these extra defenses lower the T12’s overall speed and handling, the addition of treads provide increased performance in less than ideal terrain.

TanketteFlameC.Description: The first T-class tankette to utilize this sturdier frame and versatile treads, the Vesta also represents the Velian’s first foray into fire weapons. The “Vesta” boasts a light flame turret and ample storage for the additional fuel supply required.

TanketteOffensiveC.Description: A bombastic variant of the T12 Tankette, the “Ixion” provides its crew with more support and a mounted Infantry Support Gun. Added weight from the armour results in reduced overall speed.

TruckC.Description: A heavy-duty Colonial truck used to mobilize troops and supplies.

TruckDefensiveW.Description: A heavy, reinforced Dunne transport. Fitted with a heavier frame, the Leatherback is capable of enduring more punishment at the cost of initial acceleration.

TruckMobilityC.Description: This variation of the standard R-5 Hauler is fitted with an improved suspension and axle system resulting in better overall handling. However, these improvements may not hold up under severe weather conditions.

TruckMobilityW.Description: This standard Truck is fitted with rugged off-road treads, allowing for more efficient movement on rough terrain and conditions at the expense of maximum speed.

TruckMultiC.Description: A truck fitted with an advanced rocket propulsion rack, the “Retiarius” webs the sky with deadly, screeching rockets shot at a high frequency over long distances. Holds sixteen rockets.

TruckOffensiveC.Description: This standard Truck is fitted with Light Machinegun in place of the passenger seat. It’s well suited as an escort for convoys or lightly armoured operations.

TruckDumpC.Description: This standard Truck is fitted with a resource hopper in place of the standard cargo hold. This allows for a much greater capacity for resources at the expense of space for cargo.

TruckDumpW.Description: This standard Truck is fitted with a resource hopper in place of the standard cargo hold. This allows for a much greater capacity for resources at the expense of space for cargo.

TruckW.Description: A heavy-duty Warden truck used to mobilize troops and supplies.
